abstract: President Bush expressed sadness today over the conviction of the vice president’s former chief of staff, while a spokesman tried to douse speculation about a pardon.
snippet: President Bush expressed sadness today over the conviction of the vice president’s former chief of staff, while a spokesman tried to douse speculation about a pardon.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, March 7 — If some people imagined a verdict in the criminal trial of I. Lewis Libby Jr. would calm the political passions surrounding his fate, they may have forgotten two words with a combustible history: presidential pardon.
headline_main: Pardon Libby? Left and Right Erupt in a Fight

abstract: Workers’ trucks double-park as several renovations bring a fresh wave of change to East 93rd Street from Madison to Fifth Avenues in the Carnegie Hill Historic District.
snippet: Workers’ trucks double-park as several renovations bring a fresh wave of change to East 93rd Street from Madison to Fifth Avenues in the Carnegie Hill Historic District.
lead_paragraph: SLOPING down from the crest of Carnegie Hill, East 93rd Street from Madison to Fifth Avenues is a peaceful block in the Carnegie Hill Historic District, with a mix of old brownstones and later town-house renovations of the 1920s and 1930s. Now workers’ trucks double-park here as several renovations bring a fresh wave of change.
